Billing Period and Due Date
Meters are read monthly. There is a minimum monthly charge based on the meter size even if there is no actual usage on the meter.
Payment is due by the due date on the bill. A bill becomes delinquent if it is not paid by the due date. When an account becomes delinquent,
a 10% late fee is added to the water balance. For accounts that have a current and past due balance and payment is not received by the due
date of the bill, the service is subject to disconnect on the following business day.
If water service is terminated for non-payment, service will be restored when the water balance is paid in full, including a service fee and a
deposit or an additional deposit. For customers requesting reconnection of water service the same day the water balance must be paid in full.
plus a service fee, a deposit or an additional deposit, and a reconnection fee.
A normal billing cycle is approximately 30 days. Failure to receive a bill does not exempt the customer from timely payment or preclude
service termination.
Payments returned to the Water Works by the customer's financial institution for any reason will result in the assessment of additional
charges and possible service termination without notification.
If you feel that there is a billing error or other legitimate complaint, you must notify the Montgomery Water Works either by phone or in person
prior to the due date of the bill. This will not exempt you from paying your bill by the due date.
If for any reason a consumer's account should become delinquent, the consumer agrees to pay all
Rules & Regulations
Visit our website at www.mwwssb.com for a complete listing of our Rules and Regulations, rates and charges. Customers receiving service
from Montgomery Water Works and Sanitary Sewer Board must comply with Montgomery Water Works and Sanitary Sewer Board Rules and
Regulations.
Payment Options
a. RECURRING BANK DRAFT - Your monthly bill can automatically be deducted from your bank account. You may still receive a bill. The
bill will state your payment will be drafted from your account on the due date of the bill. There are no fees charged for using
RECURRING BANK DRAFT
b. RECURRING CREDIT CARD - Your monthly bill can automatically be charged to your credit card. You may still receive a bill. The bill will
state your payment will be charged to your credit card on the due date of the bill. There are no fees charged for using RECURRING
CREDIT CARD. There is a $1000 limit on all credit card charges.
c. ONE-TIME BANK DRAFT - You may make a one-time bank draft payment on your account at any time by accessing our telephone
system at 206-1600 or website at www.mwwssb.com. There are no fees charged for using ONE-TIME BANK DRAFT.
d. ONE-TIME CREDIT CARD - You may make a one-time credit card payment on your account at any time by accessing our telephone
system at 206-1600 or website at www.mwwssb.com. There is a fee charged for a ONE-TIME CREDIT CARD PAYMENT. There is a
$1000 limit including the fee on all credit card charges.
e. CHECK - Please be advised that the Montgomery Water Works Board processes check payments through an "electronic-check-debit
system" When you pay your bill using a check, we will electronically debit your bank account on the day we receive your payment or on
the next business day. Paying your bill using a check authorizes the Board to process the check through the electronic system.
f. KIOSK - Kiosk payment services are available 24 hours a day / 7 days a week.
Damages and Illegal Connections
Tampering with Montgomery Water Works meters, water or sewer mains, or other system components is prohibited and in violation of
Section I - G of Montgomery Water Works & Sanitary Sewer Board Rules and Regulations.
